00:12:00.303 --> 00:12:01.680 position:50% align:center
That didn't dawn on me,

00:12:01.763 --> 00:12:04.557 position:50% align:center
but I've hardly ever eaten
any animal protein, myself.

00:12:04.641 --> 00:12:06.935 position:50% align:center
So I'm not really
the expert here.

00:12:07.018 --> 00:12:09.896 position:50% align:center
[SHIGURE]
Huh, well, okay.

00:12:09.979 --> 00:12:12.691 position:50% align:center
[KOBATO] Actually, I think
you have a point, though.

00:12:12.774 --> 00:12:15.944 position:50% align:center
I'd hate to end up
disappointing everyone else.

00:12:16.027 --> 00:12:17.028 position:50% align:center
[SHIGURE]
Huh?

00:12:17.112 --> 00:12:19.406 position:50% align:center
Let's shoot for the best!

00:12:20.990 --> 00:12:22.492 position:50% align:center
You can't go wrong with fish!

00:12:22.575 --> 00:12:24.661 position:50% align:center
[SHIGURE] Are you sponsored by
a sushi company or something?

00:12:24.744 --> 00:12:26.329 position:50% align:center
[KOBATO] We'll take all the
vegetables on this shelf

00:12:26.413 --> 00:12:27.622 position:50% align:center
and this shelf, too.

00:12:27.706 --> 00:12:29.040 position:50% align:center
[SHIGURE] You really think
we can eat all that?

00:12:29.124 --> 00:12:31.251 position:50% align:center
[KOBATO] As for the meat,
one cow should do.

00:12:31.334 --> 00:12:32.502 position:50% align:center
[SHIGURE]
What're you basing this on?

00:12:32.585 --> 00:12:34.838 position:50% align:center
There's only five of us, y'know!

00:12:36.089 --> 00:12:37.757 position:50% align:center
[sighs]

00:12:39.259 --> 00:12:43.221 position:50% align:center
[KOBATO] Shigure! We should
get these fireworks, too!

00:12:43.304 --> 00:12:45.890 position:50% align:center
We'll light them up together!

00:12:45.974 --> 00:12:49.811 position:50% align:center
I admit, fireworks and barbecue
do sound like a winning team.

00:12:49.894 --> 00:12:51.604 position:50% align:center
I'm just kinda worn out.

00:12:51.688 --> 00:12:53.023 position:50% align:center
Sorry 'bout this.

00:12:53.106 --> 00:12:55.817 position:50% align:center
I feel like I'm making
everything way too complicated.

00:12:55.900 --> 00:12:58.528 position:50% align:center
I just remembered the barbecue
parties we used to have

00:12:58.611 --> 00:13:01.948 position:50% align:center
at home and my sense of
scale got all thrown off.

00:13:02.032 --> 00:13:03.074 position:50% align:center
[fireworks popping]

00:13:03.158 --> 00:13:04.534 position:50% align:center
[KOBATO]
Thank you so much for coming!

00:13:04.617 --> 00:13:08.038 position:50% align:center
[SHIGURE] I see. Your family
must be really rich, huh?

00:13:09.205 --> 00:13:12.625 position:50% align:center
Wow, I'm jealous. I've never
been to a fancy party!

00:13:12.709 --> 00:13:15.086 position:50% align:center
There's nothing good
about it, I promise.

00:13:15.170 --> 00:13:16.629 position:50% align:center
[SHIGURE grunts]

00:13:16.713 --> 00:13:19.382 position:50% align:center
But on the other hand, I am
looking forward to this party.

00:13:19.466 --> 00:13:22.594 position:50% align:center
I want to see the XO eat
a big piece of manga meat.

00:13:22.677 --> 00:13:25.722 position:50% align:center
[laughs] I'm not sure what kind
of image you're conjuring up,

00:13:25.805 --> 00:13:27.640 position:50% align:center
but it sounds funny.

00:13:32.354 --> 00:13:35.315 position:50% align:center
Something like this, I'd say.

00:13:35.398 --> 00:13:38.234 position:50% align:center
[LESLIE]
Oh my! It's so juicy!

00:13:38.318 --> 00:13:39.235 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:13:39.319 --> 00:13:41.863 position:50% align:center
What's wrong?
Does it look bad?

00:13:41.946 --> 00:13:44.866 position:50% align:center
No, no. I was just thinking
we've still got some time

00:13:44.949 --> 00:13:48.370 position:50% align:center
to kill. I'll get us
something to drink.

00:13:51.956 --> 00:13:53.333 position:50% align:center
[LESLIE]
Sit back and relax.

00:13:53.416 --> 00:13:57.712 position:50% align:center
I bet the magic's happening
between them as we speak.

00:13:57.796 --> 00:13:58.963 position:50% align:center
What's your deal today?

00:13:59.047 --> 00:14:00.298 position:50% align:center
What d'you mean?

00:14:00.382 --> 00:14:02.258 position:50% align:center
You're being a real weirdo, XO.

00:14:02.342 --> 00:14:04.886 position:50% align:center
I mean, I know you like to butt
into other people's business,

00:14:04.969 --> 00:14:06.805 position:50% align:center
but it's usually more
like a pushy aunt

00:14:06.888 --> 00:14:08.014 position:50% align:center
or a gossipy neighbor

00:14:08.098 --> 00:14:11.059 position:50% align:center
or your mom's retired
friend or whatever.

00:14:11.142 --> 00:14:13.520 position:50% align:center
I object to the fact that
I'm clearly over 50

00:14:13.603 --> 00:14:15.271 position:50% align:center
in all those examples.

00:14:15.355 --> 00:14:17.482 position:50% align:center
[SUMIRE] What I'm saying is,
you're really insistent

00:14:17.565 --> 00:14:20.026 position:50% align:center
when it comes to Shigure,
for some reason.

00:14:20.110 --> 00:14:21.528 position:50% align:center
That's true!

00:14:21.611 --> 00:14:24.948 position:50% align:center
You're right. I am
trying to help Shigure,

00:14:25.031 --> 00:14:27.117 position:50% align:center
but there's a good
reason for it.

00:14:27.200 --> 00:14:29.160 position:50% align:center
At least I think so.

00:14:33.998 --> 00:14:36.251 position:50% align:center
[VENDING MACHINE]
Please choose an item.

00:14:36.334 --> 00:14:38.712 position:50% align:center
Please choose an item.

00:14:48.388 --> 00:14:50.056 position:50% align:center
[VENDING MACHINE]
State your order, please.

00:14:50.140 --> 00:14:51.266 position:50% align:center
Uh...

00:14:51.349 --> 00:14:52.559 position:50% align:center
[BOTH]
One can of orange juice

00:14:52.642 --> 00:14:54.894 position:50% align:center
and one can of
carrot juice, please.

00:14:54.978 --> 00:14:57.897 position:50% align:center
[SHIGURE]
Hm? It's you!

00:14:57.981 --> 00:14:59.607 position:50% align:center
Wait one sec.

00:14:59.691 --> 00:15:03.486 position:50% align:center
Hey, I'm here. Yeah.
That's right. Yeah.

00:15:03.570 --> 00:15:05.780 position:50% align:center
And I ran into that boy
from the other day.

00:15:05.864 --> 00:15:09.200 position:50% align:center
Uh-huh. Uh-huh. Roger.

00:15:09.284 --> 00:15:11.327 position:50% align:center
I understand, I think.

00:15:11.411 --> 00:15:12.287 position:50% align:center
What?

00:15:12.370 --> 00:15:14.914 position:50% align:center
Kamezou, Usazou. Get him.

00:15:19.377 --> 00:15:22.547 position:50% align:center
[SHIGURE screaming]

00:15:22.630 --> 00:15:25.175 position:50% align:center
Is something the matter?
That's a lot of screaming.

00:15:25.258 --> 00:15:27.552 position:50% align:center
[SHIGURE] I'll explain later!
They're assassins!

00:15:27.635 --> 00:15:29.012 position:50% align:center
Wait, what?

00:15:31.056 --> 00:15:32.307 position:50% align:center
Those cute bunnies?

00:15:32.390 --> 00:15:34.225 position:50% align:center
[SHIGURE]
Just come with me!

00:15:39.814 --> 00:15:41.608 position:50% align:center
[SHIGURE screaming]

00:15:41.691 --> 00:15:44.819 position:50% align:center
Stay still!
I can handle these two!

00:15:44.903 --> 00:15:46.237 position:50% align:center
[SHIGURE yelps]

00:15:48.323 --> 00:15:50.992 position:50% align:center
I think I have a plan.
Distract them for me.

00:15:51.076 --> 00:15:53.578 position:50% align:center
I can try, but how?

00:15:56.122 --> 00:15:57.624 position:50% align:center
[SHIGURE grunts]

00:16:03.171 --> 00:16:04.089 position:50% align:center
It's payback time!

00:16:04.172 --> 00:16:05.382 position:50% align:center
Got it!

00:16:15.141 --> 00:16:18.436 position:50% align:center
No, Kamezou. Usazou!

00:16:19.437 --> 00:16:20.814 position:50% align:center
[NADIA]
You two are going to pay dearly

00:16:20.897 --> 00:16:23.358 position:50% align:center
for kicking them
like that, I think.

00:16:25.235 --> 00:16:26.778 position:50% align:center
It's a Scarred.

00:16:26.861 --> 00:16:28.822 position:50% align:center
How handy! It looks like Hayden

00:16:28.905 --> 00:16:31.950 position:50% align:center
was prepared for anything
this time around!

00:16:35.036 --> 00:16:36.329 position:50% align:center
[KOBATO]
So how should we handle this?

00:16:36.413 --> 00:16:38.623 position:50% align:center
[SHIGURE] If we don't run now,
we're dead.

00:16:47.173 --> 00:16:49.092 position:50% align:center
It's no good. It won't budge.

00:16:49.175 --> 00:16:51.803 position:50% align:center
Then we'd better come up
with a Plan B, and fast.

00:16:51.886 --> 00:16:54.764 position:50% align:center
We need guns. Or any
kind of weapon, really.

00:16:54.848 --> 00:16:56.057 position:50% align:center
If we go back out there,

00:16:56.141 --> 00:16:59.686 position:50% align:center
I don't know if I'll be
able to protect you.

00:16:59.769 --> 00:17:02.856 position:50% align:center
I'll go on my own
and protect myself.

00:17:02.939 --> 00:17:06.401 position:50% align:center
It's a shame, we were finally
working together back there,

00:17:06.484 --> 00:17:09.654 position:50% align:center
but I suppose everyone
has their limits.

00:17:15.744 --> 00:17:17.746 position:50% align:center
No matter what happens.

00:17:17.829 --> 00:17:19.330 position:50% align:center
[KOBATO]
Hm?

00:17:19.414 --> 00:17:21.124 position:50% align:center
No matter what happens,

00:17:21.207 --> 00:17:23.793 position:50% align:center
I shall rise to the challenge.

00:17:25.420 --> 00:17:29.007 position:50% align:center
[KOBATO] Wait. Did you just
recite a line from <i>Hungry Arts</i> ?

00:17:29.090 --> 00:17:32.135 position:50% align:center
[SHIGURE]
Huh? Oh, uh-huh. Aw, jeez.

00:17:32.218 --> 00:17:36.806 position:50% align:center
We haven't talked about it, but
you're an anime fan, too, huh?

00:17:36.890 --> 00:17:38.350 position:50% align:center
Yeah, actually.

00:17:38.433 --> 00:17:40.602 position:50% align:center
But I don't have the
same passion as you.

00:17:40.685 --> 00:17:44.147 position:50% align:center
I'm not a creator or anything.

00:17:44.230 --> 00:17:45.732 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:17:45.815 --> 00:17:50.487 position:50% align:center
[SHIGURE] Anyway. Let's give our
teamwork one more shot, partner.

00:17:51.488 --> 00:17:53.073 position:50% align:center
Okay!

00:18:07.504 --> 00:18:08.838 position:50% align:center
[SHIGURE grunts]
Your turn!

00:18:08.922 --> 00:18:10.340 position:50% align:center
Right!

00:18:16.805 --> 00:18:20.058 position:50% align:center
[SCARRED A groaning]

00:18:30.318 --> 00:18:33.697 position:50% align:center
[BOTH yelling]

00:18:33.780 --> 00:18:37.951 position:50% align:center
[SCARRED A shrieks]

00:18:46.084 --> 00:18:48.086 position:50% align:center
[LARRY, SUMIRE, LESLIE]
Cheers!

00:18:50.422 --> 00:18:52.716 position:50% align:center
Oh, well. I guess
everybody just wanted

00:18:52.799 --> 00:18:55.176 position:50% align:center
to have fun by themselves, huh?

00:18:57.345 --> 00:18:59.264 position:50% align:center
Looking good! Is it ready yet?

00:18:59.347 --> 00:19:01.224 position:50% align:center
Yeah, it should be.

00:19:06.730 --> 00:19:08.565 position:50% align:center
This is what I was
talking about before!

00:19:08.648 --> 00:19:10.358 position:50% align:center
It's like the meat
you see in manga!

00:19:10.442 --> 00:19:12.068 position:50% align:center
Yeah. I guess it is.

00:19:12.152 --> 00:19:15.405 position:50% align:center
It's really wild how much you're
into manga and all that stuff.

00:19:15.488 --> 00:19:17.574 position:50% align:center
[KOBATO]
Wait, you're not into it?

00:19:17.657 --> 00:19:20.452 position:50% align:center
Uh.

00:19:20.535 --> 00:19:24.122 position:50% align:center
Well, I enjoy it, but I can't
create it like you do.

00:19:24.205 --> 00:19:27.167 position:50% align:center
I've never tried writing or
drawing anything in my life.

00:19:27.250 --> 00:19:30.754 position:50% align:center
So it's not exactly
the same, y'know?

00:19:30.837 --> 00:19:32.589 position:50% align:center
It's just a hobby.

00:19:32.672 --> 00:19:34.883 position:50% align:center
I watched it a lot and acted
like I was an expert,

00:19:34.966 --> 00:19:37.427 position:50% align:center
but didn't know
anything, really.

00:19:37.510 --> 00:19:40.305 position:50% align:center
Even if I like it, so what?

00:19:40.388 --> 00:19:44.392 position:50% align:center
It's not something for me
to be proud of, exactly.

00:19:44.476 --> 00:19:46.436 position:50% align:center
When I saw that you
were an artist,

00:19:46.519 --> 00:19:49.606 position:50% align:center
that you liked the same stuff,
but on a whole different level,

00:19:49.689 --> 00:19:52.525 position:50% align:center
it made it hard to talk to you.

00:19:52.609 --> 00:19:56.446 position:50% align:center
I see. I didn't realize that
that's what was going on.

00:19:56.529 --> 00:19:58.448 position:50% align:center
I thought you were
just being weird,

00:19:58.531 --> 00:20:00.742 position:50% align:center
'cause of my leg.

00:20:00.825 --> 00:20:04.245 position:50% align:center
Your leg? You mean
your prosthetic one?

00:20:04.329 --> 00:20:06.039 position:50% align:center
What about it?

00:20:09.167 --> 00:20:10.669 position:50% align:center
[KOBATO]
Nothing.

00:20:13.713 --> 00:20:16.049 position:50% align:center
I'm just glad I was mistaken.

00:20:18.343 --> 00:20:20.637 position:50% align:center
Aw man, I'm the worst.

00:20:20.720 --> 00:20:23.640 position:50% align:center
I couldn't find something in
life to really devote myself to.

00:20:23.723 --> 00:20:25.600 position:50% align:center
That's why I became a Sleeper.

00:20:25.684 --> 00:20:28.144 position:50% align:center
But nothing has changed at all.

00:20:29.771 --> 00:20:31.481 position:50% align:center
Do you really believe
that's true?

00:20:31.564 --> 00:20:32.982 position:50% align:center
[SHIGURE]
Uh?

00:20:33.066 --> 00:20:35.110 position:50% align:center
[KOBATO]
Real life was too much for me.

00:20:35.193 --> 00:20:36.861 position:50% align:center
I couldn't face it anymore,

00:20:36.945 --> 00:20:40.740 position:50% align:center
so I had no choice but to
immerse myself in manga.

00:20:40.824 --> 00:20:44.661 position:50% align:center
That's what I told
myself, at least.

00:20:44.744 --> 00:20:48.039 position:50% align:center
But you, you're working hard to
find your place in this world,

00:20:48.123 --> 00:20:50.750 position:50% align:center
and your love for anime
inspired you to do it.

00:20:50.834 --> 00:20:52.419 position:50% align:center
You think so?

00:20:52.502 --> 00:20:55.588 position:50% align:center
[KOBATO] You wanted to be
a hero, you said, right?

00:20:55.672 --> 00:20:57.424 position:50% align:center
That's why you're here?

00:21:00.301 --> 00:21:01.761 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:21:02.971 --> 00:21:06.766 position:50% align:center
[SHIGURE laughing]

00:21:17.068 --> 00:21:18.570 position:50% align:center
[KOBATO]
Did I get it wrong?

00:21:18.653 --> 00:21:22.073 position:50% align:center
You weren't saying all of that
just to sound cool, were you?

00:21:24.951 --> 00:21:28.788 position:50% align:center
'Course not. I'll keep trying!

00:21:33.960 --> 00:21:34.961 position:50% align:center
[KOBATO]
Me, too.

00:21:35.045 --> 00:21:37.464 position:50% align:center
I had convinced myself
that I was weak,

00:21:37.547 --> 00:21:39.507 position:50% align:center
but I know there's a
better, stronger me

00:21:39.591 --> 00:21:41.384 position:50% align:center
out there somewhere.

00:21:50.643 --> 00:21:53.813 position:50% align:center
[SHIGURE]
Good luck... to both of us.

00:21:59.652 --> 00:22:01.613 position:50% align:center
[MAN A]
She was very forthcoming.

00:22:01.696 --> 00:22:03.782 position:50% align:center
The plan will happen
as scheduled.

00:22:03.865 --> 00:22:07.452 position:50% align:center
In two weeks, there will be some
kind of event in the Asylum.

00:22:07.535 --> 00:22:10.372 position:50% align:center
It seems they'll
all be in attendance.

00:22:10.455 --> 00:22:14.834 position:50% align:center
It's about to be party time.
For all of us, I think.